This paper is about deep learning-based semantic segmentation methods for medical image analysis. The paper proposes two new models based on U-Net, which is a popular architecture for medical image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of residual networks and recurrent convolutional neural networks, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed models on benchmark datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
